ebb9a60f-2629-4465-aafe-1ae420806219.00364f28-2087-4ed5-ad23-82f5725a4fe1.transition.description=The given path is not a directory. ebb9a60f-2629-4465-aafe-1ae420806219.0ca6f844-72d7-4060-a3ac-424bee6d116b.description= 
Checks to see if a path points to a directory.

Input Parameters\:
Source - the path to check
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path does not point to a directory.
success			- The operation succeeded.
ebb9a60f-2629-4465-aafe-1ae420806219.0dd9ca52-0a75-492b-b58d-9e4ffb11fdfe.description= 
Compares a files last modified date/time to a given threshold.

Input Parameters\:
Source - the file to read
threshold - the threshold to compare the file modified time to (MM/dd/YYYY h\:mm\:ss a format  Feb 6, 2007 3\:06\:33 PM).
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The file probably could not be found.
greater than	- The file's modified time is larger than the threshold.
less than		- The file's modified time is smaller than the threshold.
equal to		- The file's modified time is the same as the threshold.

Extra Results\:
date			- The file's modified time.

Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. ebb9a60f-2629-4465-aafe-1ae420806219.5ca4518a-eb2b-47ec-a599-2e1eb42f135b.description=
Gets a list of one or more Elements in a list that match a given filter.

Inputs\:
list - the list to search.
delimiter - The delimiter that separates elements in list.
compareTo - The string to compare each element in the list against.
matchType - The type of match to perform.

Responses\:
success - 1 or more elements were found that matched.
failure - no elements matched, or something went wrong.

Returns\:
A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.

Results\:
others - all elements that did not match
matches - A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.
ebb9a60f-2629-4465-aafe-1ae420806219.5cb6fca9-65dd-4efa-a919-f4d330a19cad.description=Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. ebb9a60f-2629-4465-aafe-1ae420806219.5e2d31b1-94d6-4906-8b52-1ca4b48e7633.description=

Source - full path to file/directory to be removed (can be a UNC path)

Responses\:

Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
Source - the directory to check
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - the number of children.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success			- The operation succeeded.

ebb9a60f-2629-4465-aafe-1ae420806219.c3be5b8e-8546-4382-9e96-0364d6e4f989.prompt=Enter the date (mm/dd/yyyy hh\:mm\:ss) \: ebb9a60f-2629-4465-aafe-1ae420806219.ca5832ef-79ca-4883-99bf-2d7a7ce6b561.prompt=Enter the password\: ebb9a60f-2629-4465-aafe-1ae420806219.cf97d278-4dd1-431d-a175-2a4e91a54bf0.transition.description=The directory ${directory} has no children with the extension ${extension}. ebb9a60f-2629-4465-aafe-1ae420806219.description=
To Delete files with specified extension in local machine with an optional date input.

Inputs \:
directory		- Path of the folder in which the delete operation has to be performed.
extension		- Extension of the files that have to be deleted.
time		- The date before which the files have to be deleted. (this input is an optional one).
user		- User credentials of the system in which the delete operation has to be performed.
password		- Password of the particular user in the system in which the delete operation has to be performed.

Responses \:
success		- if the desired delete operation performed successfully.
failure		- any error occurs while executing  the flow.
